-- в”Ђв”Ђ 6sense в”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђ
UPDATE tools SET
  short_description = COALESCE($q$A B2B revenue intelligence platform that uses intent data and predictive AI to identify in-market accounts and orchestrate marketing and sales outreach across channels.$q$, short_description),
  pricing_model = COALESCE($q$freemium$q$, pricing_model),
  starting_price = COALESCE($q$Free Sales Intelligence plan available; paid plans are custom-quoted and typically start in the tens of thousands of dollars per year$q$, starting_price),
  founded_year = COALESCE(2013, founded_year),
  company_size = COALESCE(NULL, company_size),
  headquarters = COALESCE($q$San Francisco, California, United States$q$, headquarters),
  languages = ARRAY[$q$English$q$]::text[],
  seo_title = COALESCE($q$6sense Review 2026: Features, Pricing and ABM Platform Guide$q$, seo_title),
  seo_meta_description = COALESCE($q$Learn how 6sense combines intent data and predictive AI for account-based marketing, plus its pricing model, key features, pros and cons, and top use cases.$q$, seo_meta_description),
  llm_readable_summary = COALESCE($q$6sense is a B2B revenue intelligence and account-based marketing (ABM) platform founded in 2013 and headquartered in San Francisco, California. The platform combines proprietary intent data, predictive AI models, and omni-channel orchestration into a single system spanning marketing, sales, and revenue operations teams. Its core premise is that most B2B buying research happens anonymously online before a prospect ever fills out a form or talks to sales; 6sense claims to de-anonymize this behavior by tracking intent signals across the web (using its own data network plus third-party intent feeds) and mapping them to specific accounts. Predictive AI scoring then estimates which accounts are actively in a buying cycle and which stage of that cycle they are likely in, so go-to-market teams can prioritize outreach toward accounts that are more likely to convert. Once accounts are identified, 6sense provides orchestration tools to run targeted advertising, personalized website experiences, and email sequences, along with sales intelligence features such as contact and company data, buying-stage alerts, and a Chrome extension for prospecting. The platform is built for account-based go-to-market motions rather than high-volume, low-touch demand generation, and it is most commonly adopted by mid-market and enterprise B2B companies that already have a defined ideal customer profile (ICP), a reasonably large total addressable market, and dedicated marketing operations or revenue operations staff to manage the platform. 6sense offers a free tier of its Sales Intelligence product that includes a limited number of monthly data credits along with basic account search, buying alerts, list building, and the Chrome extension, which functions as a lead-generation funnel into its paid plans. Full platform access, including predictive AI, advertising orchestration, and enterprise-grade intent data, is sold through custom, quote-based contracts; publicly reported pricing benchmarks place team-level plans starting around the mid five figures annually, with mid-market deployments commonly landing in the six-figure range and large enterprise contracts exceeding that. There is no public self-serve checkout for the full platform, so prospective buyers work with 6sense's sales team to scope a package based on account volume, data needs, and orchestration channels required. Competitors in the ABM and intent-data category include Demandbase, ZoomInfo, Clearbit (now part of HubSpot), and Bombora as a data-only alternative.$q$, llm_readable_summary),
  status = 'published',
  noindex = false,
  sitemap_eligible = true,
  published_at = COALESCE(published_at, now()),
  updated_at = now()
WHERE id = '8dd2ba58-481a-4ed0-846c-96234a88944e';

